IDENTIFICATION: We consulted descriptions and measurements of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[944,1212,1226,1250]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Mesophylla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macconnelli">
<emphasis box="[944,1212,1226,1250]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="25">Mesophylla macconnelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Goodwin, G. G. &amp; A. M. Greenhall" box="[837,1207,1260,1284]" pageId="25" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 18" refId="ref36439" refString="Goodwin, G. G., and A. M. Greenhall. 1962. Two new bats from Trinidad, with comments on the status of the genus Mesophylla. American Museum Novitates 2080: 1 - 18." type="journal article" year="1962">Goodwin and Greenhall (1962)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ceballos Bendezu" box="[684,961,1294,1319]" pageId="25" pageNumber="25" pagination="7 - 60" refId="ref33872" refString="Ceballos Bendezu, I. 1968. Quiropteros del departamento de Loreto (Peru). Revista de la Facultad de Ciencias, Universidad Nacional de San Antonio Abad del Cuzco 2: 7 - 60." type="journal article" year="1968">Ceballos Bendezú (1968)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Starrett, A. &amp; R. Casebeer" pageId="25" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref42619" refString="Starrett, A., and R. Casebeer. 1968. Records of bats from Costa Rica. Registros de murcielagos de Costa Rica. Contributions in Science (Los Angeles) 148: 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="1968">Starrett and Casebeer (1968)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Carter, D. C. &amp; P. G. Dolan" box="[770,1040,1329,1353]" pageId="25" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 136" refId="ref33829" refString="Carter, D. C., and P. G. Dolan. 1978. Catalogue of type specimens of Neotropical bats in selected European museums. Special Publication of the Museum of Texas Tech University 15: 1 - 136." type="journal article" year="1978">Carter and Dolan (1978)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Swanepoel, P. &amp; H. H. Genoways" pageId="25" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 441" refId="ref42730" refString="Swanepoel, P., and H. H. Genoways. 1979. Morphometrics. In R. J. Baker, J. K. Jones, Jr., and D. C. Carter (editors), Biology of bats of the New World family Phyllostomatidae, Part III: 1 - 441. Special Publications, Texas Tech University Museum 16." type="journal article" year="1979">Swanepoel and Genoways (1979)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Brosset, A. &amp; P. Charles-Dominique" pageId="25" pageNumber="25" pagination="509 - 560" refId="ref33466" refString="Brosset, A., and P. Charles-Dominique. 1990. The bats from French Guiana: a taxonomic, faunistic and ecological approach. Mammalia 54: 509 - 560." type="journal article" year="1990">Brosset and Charles-Dominique (1990)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Anderson, S." box="[847,1041,1397,1421]" pageId="25" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 652" refId="ref32736" refString="Anderson, S. 1997. Mammals of Bolivia: taxonomy and distribution. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 231: 1 - 652." type="journal article" year="1997">Anderson (1997)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Simmons, N. B. &amp; R. S. Voss" pageId="25" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 219" refId="ref42345" refString="Simmons, N. B., and R. S. Voss. 1998. The mammals of Paracou, French Guiana: a Neotropical lowland rainforest fauna. Part 1. Bats. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 237: 1 - 219." type="journal article" year="1998">Simmons and Voss (1998)</bibRefCitation>
. No subspecies are currently recognized in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Arroyo-Cabrales, 2008 a)" baseAuthorityName="Arroyo-Cabrales" baseAuthorityYear="2008" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Mesophylla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macconnelli">
<emphasis box="[840,1006,1465,1489]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="25">M. macconnelli</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Arroyo-Cabrales, J." pageId="25" pageNumber="25" pagination="327 - 329" refId="ref32764" refString="Arroyo-Cabrales, J. 2008 a (&quot; 2007 &quot;). Genus Mesophylla O. Thomas, 1901. In A. L. Gardner (editor), Mammals of South America, vol. 1: Marsupials, xenarthrans, shrews, and bats: 327 - 329. Chicago: University of Chicago Press." type="book chapter" year="2008">Arroyo-Cabrales, 2008a</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Our Mayo River basin specimens exhibit the diagnostic characteristics of the species: small size (FA 
<quantity box="[843,962,1568,1592]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" metricValueMax="3.4" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="25" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="31.0" valueMax="34.0" valueMin="28.0">28–34 mm</quantity>
); ears and noseleaf yellow in live specimens, but paler in museum specimens; small accessory noseleaflike structure present behind the noseleaf; skull short with a relatively narrow rostrum; palate extending well behind the last molars; upper inner incisors long, convergent, and usually with weakly bifid tips; m2 lacking a posterior cuspulid; and minute m3 (
<bibRefCitation author="Arroyo-Cabrales, J." box="[196,460,329,353]" pageId="26" pageNumber="26" pagination="327 - 329" refId="ref32764" refString="Arroyo-Cabrales, J. 2008 a (&quot; 2007 &quot;). Genus Mesophylla O. Thomas, 1901. In A. L. Gardner (editor), Mammals of South America, vol. 1: Marsupials, xenarthrans, shrews, and bats: 327 - 329. Chicago: University of Chicago Press." type="book chapter" year="2008">Arroyo-Cabrales, 2008a</bibRefCitation>
). Measurements of our specimens fall within the range reported for the species.
</paragraph>
